This paper deals with privacy-preserving deep learning, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a new method for delivering data for training and inference with privacy preservation, which involves data morphing and augmented convolutional layers. This method is specifically designed for deep learning, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the computational overhead and data transmission overhead of the proposed method, which involves optimization techniques, and this could fall under the category of computer systems and networking (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
